To make an `h1` text uppercase, you can apply the CSS `text-transform` property and set its value to `uppercase`. Here's an example:

```html
<style>
  h1 {
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
</style>

<h1>This text will be displayed in uppercase</h1>
```

In this code snippet, the `text-transform: uppercase;` property is added to the `h1` element style using `<style>` tags. This will transform the text inside the `h1` element to be displayed in uppercase.
